div.h3: COUNT(*) vs COUNT(col) and NULL-skipping in SUM/AVG

g.text: SUM and AVG: NULL Skipping Behavior

ol.li: COUNT(*) counts rows, COUNT(col) counts non-NULL values
SUM/AVG skip NULLs entirelythey don't propagate NULL
Empty set returns NULL for SUM/AVG, 0 for COUNT(*)
AVG divides by non-NULL count, not total row count

div.p: In aggregates: SUM skips NULLs (NULLs excluded from calculation)
Counts ALL rows regardless of NULLs
Counts only NON-NULL values in bonus column
Division by COUNT of non-NULL values (NOT by total row count!)

ul.li: SUM of no values is "unknown" NULL
AVG of no values is "unknown" NULL
COUNT(*) of no rows is definitively 0

div.p: This is not the same as SUM of NULLs!
